{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":767,"text":"To be honest, by personality,"},{"time":3619,"text":"I'm just not much of a crier."},{"time":7316,"text":"But I think in my career\nthat's been a good thing."},{"time":11246,"text":"I'm a civil rights lawyer,"},{"time":12630,"text":"and I've seen some \nhorrible things in the world."},{"time":17034,"text":"I began my career working \npolice abuse cases in the United States."},{"time":20844,"text":"And then in 1994, I was sent to Rwanda"},{"time":24318,"text":"to be the director of the U.N.'s \ngenocide investigation."},{"time":29908,"text":"It turns out that tears \njust aren't much help"},{"time":33647,"text":"when you're trying \nto investigate a genocide."},{"time":37176,"text":"The things I had to see, \nand feel and touch"},{"time":42037,"text":"were pretty unspeakable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45534,"text":"What I can tell you is this:"},{"time":48891,"text":"that the Rwandan genocide"},{"time":50988,"text":"was one of the world's\ngreatest failures of simple compassion."},{"time":57711,"text":"That word, compassion, actually \ncomes from two Latin words:"},{"time":61120,"text":"cum passio, which simply mean \n\"to suffer with.\""},{"time":66642,"text":"And the things that I saw and experienced"},{"time":70204,"text":"in Rwanda as I got up close\nto human suffering,"},{"time":72790,"text":"it did, in moments, move me to tears."},{"time":76129,"text":"But I just wish that I, \nand the rest of the world,"},{"time":78855,"text":"had been moved earlier."},{"time":81370,"text":"And not just to tears,"},{"time":83034,"text":"but to actually stop the genocide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86834,"text":"Now by contrast, I've also been involved"},{"time":89292,"text":"with one of the world's greatest\nsuccesses of compassion."},{"time":95125,"text":"And that's the fight against \nglobal poverty."},{"time":98071,"text":"It's a cause that probably\nhas involved all of us here."},{"time":100854,"text":"I don't know if your first introduction"},{"time":102852,"text":"might have been choruses of\n\"We Are the World,\""},{"time":106217,"text":"or maybe the picture of a sponsored child\non your refrigerator door,"},{"time":110280,"text":"or maybe the birthday you\ndonated for fresh water."},{"time":114367,"text":"I don't really remember what my first\nintroduction to poverty was"},{"time":117581,"text":"but I do remember the most jarring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121145,"text":"It was when I met Venus --"},{"time":123307,"text":"she's a mom from Zambia."},{"time":126029,"text":"She's got three kids and she's a widow."},{"time":129655,"text":"When I met her, she had walked\nabout 12 miles"},{"time":133022,"text":"in the only garments she owned,"},{"time":135695,"text":"to come to the capital city\nand to share her story."},{"time":139957,"text":"She sat down with me for hours,"},{"time":143572,"text":"just ushered me in to \nthe world of poverty."},{"time":148097,"text":"She described what it was like \nwhen the coals on the cooking fire"},{"time":151238,"text":"finally just went completely cold."},{"time":154967,"text":"When that last drop \nof cooking oil finally ran out."},{"time":159729,"text":"When the last of the food, \ndespite her best efforts,"},{"time":163585,"text":"ran out."},{"time":166113,"text":"She had to watch her youngest son, Peter,"},{"time":169096,"text":"suffer from malnutrition,"},{"time":171878,"text":"as his legs just slowly bowed \ninto uselessness."},{"time":175954,"text":"As his eyes grew cloudy and dim."},{"time":179302,"text":"And then as Peter finally grew cold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186130,"text":"For over 50 years, stories like this\nhave been moving us to compassion."},{"time":191811,"text":"We whose kids have plenty to eat."},{"time":194661,"text":"And we're moved not only \nto care about global poverty,"},{"time":197330,"text":"but to actually try to do our part \nto stop the suffering."},{"time":202020,"text":"Now there's plenty of room for critique \nthat we haven't done enough,"},{"time":205493,"text":"and what it is that we've done\nhasn't been effective enough,"},{"time":209715,"text":"but the truth is this:"},{"time":212845,"text":"The fight against global poverty\nis probably the broadest,"},{"time":216396,"text":"longest running manifestation of the \nhuman phenomenon of compassion"},{"time":221531,"text":"in the history of our species."},{"time":224673,"text":"And so I'd like to share\na pretty shattering insight"},{"time":228322,"text":"that might forever change the way\nyou think about that struggle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232615,"text":"But first, let me begin with what\nyou probably already know."},{"time":235438,"text":"Thirty-five years ago, when I would have\nbeen graduating from high school,"},{"time":238920,"text":"they told us that 40,000 kids every day\ndied because of poverty."},{"time":245297,"text":"That number, today, is now \ndown to 17,000."},{"time":249669,"text":"Way too many, of course,"},{"time":251675,"text":"but it does mean that every year,"},{"time":254352,"text":"there's eight million kids who\ndon't have to die from poverty."},{"time":259650,"text":"Moreover, the number of \npeople in our world"},{"time":262067,"text":"who are living in extreme poverty,"},{"time":264230,"text":"which is defined as living off\nabout a dollar and a quarter a day,"},{"time":267567,"text":"that has fallen from 50 percent,"},{"time":271179,"text":"to only 15 percent."},{"time":275403,"text":"This is massive progress,"},{"time":276853,"text":"and this exceeds everybody's \nexpectations about what is possible."},{"time":282258,"text":"And I think you and I,"},{"time":285123,"text":"I think, honestly, that we can \nfeel proud and encouraged"},{"time":289399,"text":"to see the way that compassion \nactually has the power"},{"time":293284,"text":"to succeed in stopping \nthe suffering of millions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298476,"text":"But here's the part that you \nmight not hear very much about."},{"time":302852,"text":"If you move that poverty mark just\nup to two dollars a day,"},{"time":307586,"text":"it turns out that virtually \nthe same two billion people"},{"time":310585,"text":"who were stuck in that harsh poverty\nwhen I was in high school,"},{"time":314397,"text":"are still stuck there,"},{"time":316278,"text":"35 years later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318667,"text":"So why, why are so many billions\nstill stuck in such harsh poverty?"},{"time":324396,"text":"Well, let's think about\nVenus for a moment."},{"time":327351,"text":"Now for decades, my wife and I have been\nmoved by common compassion"},{"time":331123,"text":"to sponsor kids, to fund microloans,"},{"time":333952,"text":"to support generous levels of foreign aid."},{"time":337471,"text":"But until I had actually talked to Venus,"},{"time":340563,"text":"I would have had no idea that \nnone of those approaches"},{"time":343200,"text":"actually addressed why she had\nto watch her son die."},{"time":349806,"text":"\"We were doing fine,\" Venus told me,"},{"time":354243,"text":"\"until Brutus started to cause trouble.\""},{"time":358785,"text":"Now, Brutus is Venus' neighbor \nand \"cause trouble\""},{"time":361755,"text":"is what happened the day after\nVenus' husband died,"},{"time":365281,"text":"when Brutus just came and threw\nVenus and the kids out of the house,"},{"time":369213,"text":"stole all their land, and robbed\ntheir market stall."},{"time":374385,"text":"You see, Venus was thrown \ninto destitution by violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380882,"text":"And then it occurred to me, of course,"},{"time":382891,"text":"that none of my child sponsorships,\nnone of the microloans,"},{"time":386690,"text":"none of the traditional \nanti-poverty programs"},{"time":390552,"text":"were going to stop Brutus,"},{"time":394518,"text":"because they weren't meant to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397872,"text":"This became even more clear\nto me when I met Griselda."},{"time":402878,"text":"She's a marvelous young girl\nliving in a very poor community"},{"time":407097,"text":"in Guatemala."},{"time":408913,"text":"And one of the things\nwe've learned over the years"},{"time":411310,"text":"is that perhaps the most powerful thing"},{"time":413881,"text":"that Griselda and her family can do"},{"time":416725,"text":"to get Griselda and her family \nout of poverty"},{"time":419390,"text":"is to make sure that she goes to school."},{"time":422514,"text":"The experts call this the Girl Effect."},{"time":427239,"text":"But when we met Griselda, \nshe wasn't going to school."},{"time":431321,"text":"In fact, she was rarely ever \nleaving her home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436388,"text":"Days before we met her,"},{"time":438173,"text":"while she was walking home\nfrom church with her family,"},{"time":440818,"text":"in broad daylight,"},{"time":443133,"text":"men from her community \njust snatched her off the street,"},{"time":446610,"text":"and violently raped her."},{"time":449708,"text":"See, Griselda had every\nopportunity to go to school,"},{"time":454205,"text":"it just wasn't safe for her to get there."},{"time":457626,"text":"And Griselda's not the only one."},{"time":460466,"text":"Around the world, poor women and girls"},{"time":463190,"text":"between the ages of 15 and 44,"},{"time":468301,"text":"they are -- when victims of \nthe everyday violence"},{"time":472386,"text":"of domestic abuse and sexual violence --"},{"time":475872,"text":"those two forms of violence account\nfor more death and disability"},{"time":480684,"text":"than malaria, than car accidents,\nthan war combined."},{"time":491298,"text":"The truth is, the poor of our world\nare trapped in whole systems of violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496075,"text":"In South Asia, for instance,\nI could drive past this rice mill"},{"time":500108,"text":"and see this man hoisting \nthese 100-pound sacks"},{"time":503045,"text":"of rice upon his thin back."},{"time":505089,"text":"But I would have no idea, until later,"},{"time":506907,"text":"that he was actually a slave,"},{"time":509349,"text":"held by violence in that rice mill\nsince I was in high school."},{"time":514828,"text":"Decades of anti-poverty programs\nright in his community"},{"time":518239,"text":"were never able to rescue him\nor any of the hundred other slaves"},{"time":522321,"text":"from the beatings and the rapes\nand the torture"},{"time":525957,"text":"of violence inside the rice mill."},{"time":529652,"text":"In fact, half a century of \nanti-poverty programs"},{"time":534032,"text":"have left more poor people in slavery"},{"time":537706,"text":"than in any other time in human history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541071,"text":"Experts tell us that there's about\n35 million people in slavery today."},{"time":547050,"text":"That's about the population \nof the entire nation of Canada,"},{"time":550711,"text":"where we're sitting today."},{"time":554179,"text":"This is why, over time, I have come\nto call this epidemic of violence"},{"time":557483,"text":"the Locust Effect."},{"time":559772,"text":"Because in the lives of the poor,\nit just descends like a plague"},{"time":562783,"text":"and it destroys everything."},{"time":565571,"text":"In fact, now when you survey\nvery, very poor communities,"},{"time":569954,"text":"residents will tell you that their\ngreatest fear is violence."},{"time":574038,"text":"But notice the violence that they fear"},{"time":576607,"text":"is not the violence of \ngenocide or the wars,"},{"time":579785,"text":"it's everyday violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582140,"text":"So for me, as a lawyer, of course,\nmy first reaction was to think,"},{"time":585353,"text":"well, of course we've\ngot to change all the laws."},{"time":587667,"text":"We've got to make all this violence\nagainst the poor illegal."},{"time":591167,"text":"But then I found out, it already is."},{"time":594902,"text":"The problem is not that \nthe poor don't get laws,"},{"time":597742,"text":"it's that they don't get law enforcement."},{"time":602542,"text":"In the developing world,"},{"time":604185,"text":"basic law enforcement systems\nare so broken"},{"time":607250,"text":"that recently the U.N. issued \na report that found"},{"time":610416,"text":"that \"most poor people live\noutside the protection of the law.\""},{"time":616020,"text":"Now honestly, you and I have \njust about no idea"},{"time":618412,"text":"of what that would mean"},{"time":620009,"text":"because we have no \nfirst-hand experience of it."},{"time":623688,"text":"Functioning law enforcement for us \nis just a total assumption."},{"time":626765,"text":"In fact, nothing expresses that assumption\nmore clearly than three simple numbers:"},{"time":631137,"text":"9-1-1,"},{"time":633598,"text":"which, of course, is the number\nfor the emergency police operator"},{"time":636765,"text":"here in Canada and in the United States,"},{"time":640066,"text":"where the average response time \nto a police 911 emergency call"},{"time":644147,"text":"is about 10 minutes."},{"time":645810,"text":"So we take this just \ncompletely for granted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648995,"text":"But what if there was no \nlaw enforcement to protect you?"},{"time":654582,"text":"A woman in Oregon recently\nexperienced what this would be like."},{"time":659204,"text":"She was home alone in her \ndark house on a Saturday night,"},{"time":663545,"text":"when a man started to tear \nhis way into her home."},{"time":666510,"text":"This was her worst nightmare,"},{"time":668467,"text":"because this man had actually put her\nin the hospital from an assault"},{"time":673075,"text":"just two weeks before."},{"time":675193,"text":"So terrified, she picks up that phone\nand does what any of us would do:"},{"time":678551,"text":"She calls 911 --"},{"time":681196,"text":"but only to learn that because \nof budget cuts in her county,"},{"time":686028,"text":"law enforcement wasn't available \non the weekends."},{"time":689397,"text":"Listen."},{"time":690187,"text":"Dispatcher: I don't have anybody \nto send out there."},{"time":693006,"text":"Woman: OK"},{"time":694023,"text":"Dispatcher: Um, obviously if he comes\ninside the residence and assaults you,"},{"time":698126,"text":"can you ask him to go away?"},{"time":699799,"text":"Or do you know if\nhe is intoxicated or anything?"},{"time":702042,"text":"Woman: I've already asked him.\nI've already told him I was calling you."},{"time":705415,"text":"He's broken in before,\nbusted down my door, assaulted me."},{"time":708088,"text":"Dispatcher: Uh-huh."},{"time":709033,"text":"Woman: Um, yeah, so ..."},{"time":710186,"text":"Dispatcher: Is there any way you could\nsafely leave the residence?"},{"time":713405,"text":"Woman: No, I can't, because he's blocking\npretty much my only way out."},{"time":716822,"text":"Dispatcher: Well, the only thing I can do \nis give you some advice,"},{"time":719968,"text":"and call the sheriff's office tomorrow."},{"time":722684,"text":"Obviously, if he comes in and\nunfortunately has a weapon"},{"time":727496,"text":"or is trying to cause you physical harm,\nthat's a different story."},{"time":730822,"text":"You know, the sheriff's office\ndoesn't work up there."},{"time":733489,"text":"I don't have anybody to send.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":737735,"text":"Gary Haugen: Tragically, the woman \ninside that house"},{"time":740388,"text":"was violently assaulted, choked and raped\n"},{"time":746327,"text":"because this is what it means to live\noutside the rule of law."},{"time":753841,"text":"And this is where billions\nof our poorest live."},{"time":760015,"text":"What does that look like?"},{"time":762443,"text":"In Bolivia, for example, if a man \nsexually assaults a poor child,"},{"time":766871,"text":"statistically, he's at greater risk\nof slipping in the shower and dying"},{"time":771544,"text":"than he is of ever going \nto jail for that crime."},{"time":776002,"text":"In South Asia, if you \nenslave a poor person,"},{"time":780687,"text":"you're at greater risk of being \nstruck by lightning"},{"time":783610,"text":"than ever being sent \nto jail for that crime."},{"time":786660,"text":"And so the epidemic of everyday \nviolence, it just rages on."},{"time":791639,"text":"And it devastates our efforts to try\nto help billions of people"},{"time":795738,"text":"out of their two-dollar-a-day hell."},{"time":799315,"text":"Because the data just doesn't lie."},{"time":801817,"text":"It turns out that you can give \nall manner of goods and services"},{"time":804876,"text":"to the poor,"},{"time":806029,"text":"but if you don't restrain the hands \nof the violent bullies"},{"time":809155,"text":"from taking it all away,"},{"time":810990,"text":"you're going to be very disappointed\nin the long-term impact of your efforts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815889,"text":"So you would think that the disintegration\nof basic law enforcement"},{"time":819660,"text":"in the developing world\nwould be a huge priority"},{"time":822675,"text":"for the global fight against poverty."},{"time":825915,"text":"But it's not."},{"time":829028,"text":"Auditors of international assistance\nrecently couldn't find"},{"time":832825,"text":"even one percent of aid going \nto protect the poor"},{"time":836659,"text":"from the lawless chaos \nof everyday violence."},{"time":840990,"text":"And honestly, when we do talk about \nviolence against the poor,"},{"time":844296,"text":"sometimes it's in the weirdest of ways."},{"time":847805,"text":"A fresh water organization tells\na heart-wrenching story"},{"time":850888,"text":"of girls who are raped on the way\nto fetching water,"},{"time":854480,"text":"and then celebrates\nthe solution of a new well"},{"time":858290,"text":"that drastically shortens their walk."},{"time":861745,"text":"End of story."},{"time":864863,"text":"But not a word about the rapists who\nare still right there in the community."},{"time":871813,"text":"If a young woman on one \nof our college campuses"},{"time":874127,"text":"was raped on her walk to the library, \n"},{"time":877273,"text":"we would never celebrate the solution\nof moving the library closer to the dorm."},{"time":883121,"text":"And yet, for some reason,\nthis is okay for poor people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888915,"text":"Now the truth is, the traditional experts"},{"time":891469,"text":"in economic development\nand poverty alleviation,"},{"time":893775,"text":"they don't know how to fix this problem."},{"time":896035,"text":"And so what happens?"},{"time":897856,"text":"They don't talk about it."},{"time":901237,"text":"But the more fundamental reason"},{"time":905408,"text":"that law enforcement for the poor\nin the developing world"},{"time":908188,"text":"is so neglected,"},{"time":910072,"text":"is because the people inside\nthe developing world, with money,"},{"time":913957,"text":"don't need it."},{"time":917165,"text":"I was at the World Economic \nForum not long ago"},{"time":919745,"text":"talking to corporate executives who have\nmassive businesses in the developing world"},{"time":923689,"text":"and I was just asking them,"},{"time":925771,"text":"\"How do you guys protect all your people\nand property from all the violence?\""},{"time":931325,"text":"And they looked at each other, \nand they said, practically in unison,"},{"time":936147,"text":"\"We buy it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":939474,"text":"Indeed, private security forces \nin the developing world"},{"time":943336,"text":"are now, four, five and seven times\nlarger than the public police force."},{"time":950146,"text":"In Africa, the largest employer \non the continent now is private security."},{"time":958884,"text":"But see, the rich can pay for safety\nand can keep getting richer,"},{"time":962702,"text":"but the poor can't pay for it\nand they're left totally unprotected"},{"time":966504,"text":"and they keep getting thrown\nto the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970464,"text":"This is a massive and scandalous outrage."},{"time":974896,"text":"And it doesn't have to be this way."},{"time":977849,"text":"Broken law enforcement can be fixed."},{"time":980416,"text":"Violence can be stopped."},{"time":982496,"text":"Almost all criminal justice systems,\n"},{"time":984888,"text":"they start out broken and corrupt,"},{"time":987417,"text":"but they can be transformed\nby fierce effort and commitment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991687,"text":"The path forward is really pretty clear."},{"time":993930,"text":"Number one: We have to start making"},{"time":997377,"text":"stopping violence indispensable \nto the fight against poverty."},{"time":1001144,"text":"In fact, any conversation\nabout global poverty\n"},{"time":1003578,"text":"that doesn't include the problem \nof violence must be deemed not serious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009416,"text":"And secondly, we have to begin \nto seriously invest resources"},{"time":1013792,"text":"and share expertise to support \nthe developing world"},{"time":1017729,"text":"as they fashion new, \npublic systems of justice,"},{"time":1021086,"text":"not private security,"},{"time":1022652,"text":"that give everybody a chance to be safe."},{"time":1026349,"text":"These transformations \nare actually possible"},{"time":1029031,"text":"and they're happening today."},{"time":1031640,"text":"Recently, the Gates Foundation \nfunded a project"},{"time":1034778,"text":"in the second largest city \nof the Philippines,"},{"time":1037254,"text":"where local advocates\nand local law enforcement"},{"time":1040260,"text":"were able to transform corrupt police\nand broken courts so drastically,"},{"time":1047118,"text":"that in just four short years,"},{"time":1049705,"text":"they were able to measurably reduce"},{"time":1052177,"text":"the commercial sexual violence \nagainst poor kids by 79 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059758,"text":"You know, from the hindsight of history,"},{"time":1063302,"text":"what's always most inexplicable\nand inexcusable"},{"time":1068859,"text":"are the simple failures of compassion."},{"time":1073480,"text":"Because I think history convenes \na tribunal of our grandchildren"},{"time":1078208,"text":"and they just ask us,"},{"time":1079969,"text":"\"Grandma, Grandpa, where were you?"},{"time":1084211,"text":"Where were you, Grandpa, when \nthe Jews were fleeing Nazi Germany"},{"time":1087766,"text":"and were being rejected from our shores?"},{"time":1089695,"text":"Where were you?"},{"time":1091823,"text":"And Grandma, where were you\nwhen they were marching"},{"time":1094223,"text":"our Japanese-American neighbors\noff to internment camps?"},{"time":1098276,"text":"And Grandpa, where were you \nwhen they were beating"},{"time":1100665,"text":"our African-American neighbors"},{"time":1102938,"text":"just because they were trying\nto register to vote?\""},{"time":1106458,"text":"Likewise, when our grandchildren ask us,"},{"time":1110702,"text":"\"Grandma, Grandpa, where were you"},{"time":1113143,"text":"when two billion of the world's poorest\nwere drowning in a lawless chaos"},{"time":1117636,"text":"of everyday violence?\""},{"time":1121287,"text":"I hope we can say that we had compassion,\nthat we raised our voice,"},{"time":1127852,"text":"and as a generation, we were moved\nto make the violence stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135684,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1138141,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1153890,"text":"Chris Anderson: Really powerfully argued."},{"time":1156785,"text":"Talk to us a bit about\nsome of the things"},{"time":1159064,"text":"that have actually been happening to,\nfor example, boost police training."},{"time":1165588,"text":"How hard a process is that?"},{"time":1167427,"text":"GH: Well, one of the glorious \nthings that's starting to happen now"},{"time":1171009,"text":"is that the collapse of these systems\nand the consequences are becoming obvious."},{"time":1175619,"text":"There's actually, now, \npolitical will to do that."},{"time":1178981,"text":"But it just requires now an investment\nof resources and transfer of expertise."},{"time":1183106,"text":"There's a political will struggle \nthat's going to take place as well,"},{"time":1186509,"text":"but those are winnable fights,"},{"time":1188324,"text":"because we've done some examples\naround the world"},{"time":1190623,"text":"at International Justice Mission\nthat are very encouraging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1193732,"text":"CA: So just tell us in one country,\nhow much it costs"},{"time":1197233,"text":"to make a material difference \nto police, for example --"},{"time":1200748,"text":"I know that's only one piece of it."},{"time":1202538,"text":"GH: In Guatemala, for instance,\nwe've started a project there"},{"time":1205754,"text":"with the local police \nand court system, prosecutors,"},{"time":1209006,"text":"to retrain them so that they can \nactually effectively bring these cases."},{"time":1212819,"text":"And we've seen prosecutions against\nperpetrators of sexual violence"},{"time":1217131,"text":"increase by more than 1,000 percent."},{"time":1219967,"text":"This project has been very modestly funded\nat about a million dollars a year,"},{"time":1224356,"text":"and the kind of bang \nyou can get for your buck"},{"time":1226662,"text":"in terms of leveraging\na criminal justice system"},{"time":1230838,"text":"that could function if it were properly\ntrained and motivated and led,"},{"time":1235595,"text":"and these countries, \nespecially a middle class"},{"time":1238138,"text":"that is seeing that there's \nreally no future"},{"time":1241282,"text":"with this total instability and\ntotal privatization of security"},{"time":1245150,"text":"I think there's an opportunity,\na window for change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1248341,"text":"CA: But to make this happen, you have\nto look at each part in the chain --"},{"time":1253421,"text":"the police, who else?"},{"time":1255676,"text":"GH: So that's the thing \nabout law enforcement,"},{"time":1257957,"text":"it starts out with the police,"},{"time":1259400,"text":"they're the front end\nof the pipeline of justice,"},{"time":1262083,"text":"but they hand if off to the prosecutors,"},{"time":1264030,"text":"and the prosecutors \nhand it off to the courts,"},{"time":1266265,"text":"and the survivors of violence \nhave to be supported by social services"},{"time":1269557,"text":"all the way through that."},{"time":1270863,"text":"So you have to do an approach \nthat pulls that all together."},{"time":1273675,"text":"In the past, there's been a little bit\nof training of the courts,"},{"time":1276726,"text":"but they get crappy evidence \nfrom the police,"},{"time":1278900,"text":"or a little police intervention \nthat has to do with narcotics or terrorism"},{"time":1282537,"text":"but nothing to do with treating\nthe common poor person"},{"time":1285405,"text":"with excellent law enforcement,"},{"time":1286924,"text":"so it's about pulling that all together,"},{"time":1288949,"text":"and you can actually have people\nin very poor communities"},{"time":1292091,"text":"experience law enforcement like us,"},{"time":1294274,"text":"which is imperfect in our \nown experience, for sure,"},{"time":1297096,"text":"but boy, is it a great thing to sense\nthat you can call 911"},{"time":1300228,"text":"and maybe someone will protect you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1303264,"text":"CA: Gary, I think you've done \na spectacular job"},{"time":1305537,"text":"of bringing this to the world's attention"},{"time":1307664,"text":"in your book and right here today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1309411,"text":"Thanks so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1310505,"text":"Gary Haugen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1311281,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}